{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A signaling NaN (“not a number”).","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"signalingNaN","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default IEEE 754 behavior of operations involving a signaling NaN is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to raise the Invalid flag in the floating-point environment and return a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"quiet NaN."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Operations on types conforming to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FloatingPoint"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"support this behavior, but they might also support other options. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, it would be reasonable to implement alternative operations in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which operating on a signaling NaN triggers a runtime error or results"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in a diagnostic for debugging purposes. Types that implement alternative"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behaviors for a signaling NaN must document the departure."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Other than these signaling operations, a signaling NaN behaves in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"same manner as a quiet NaN.","type":"text"}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/docume